<Author>cuss
<Content>Excellent with perfect location This hotel is an excellent choice for those wanting to be in close proximity to the French Quarter who also want a little peace and quiet. Hilton St. Charles is located 3 very short blocks from Canal and Royal (start of the Quarter), 1 block down from Bourbon. The walk to Canal is negligible as is a walk all the way to the other side of the Quarter at Esplanade (NOLA is flat). The St. Charles St. streetcar stops right out side and it will take you out to Tulane to the west and Esplanade to the east for a mere $1.25 + $0.25 transfer.The hotel itself is a mix of traditional and modern boutique. The staff are friendly and helpful, beds are great and some of the rooms (try and get a corner one) are HUGE. The adjacent restaurant, Luke, is excellent and fairly reasonable. People have complained about streetcar noise, which is nonsense even from the second floor right on St. Charles. Other complaints are directed at the smell of the place. Also nonsense. No complaints of any sort from me.FInally, this location in the Central Business District is apparently completely safe. It' not far enough off the beaten track to be of any concern at all.Try and get this gem from Hotwire and you will get what is very likely the single best hotel deal in the United States. I'm serious... 
