<Content>Not at all the same We stayed at the Hilton Saint Charles for three days in August. I stayed at this hotel when it was the Monaco many times, and never had a bad experience. It all began with check-in. We were to have early check-in to a suite. However when we got there they had no rooms for us, and we had to wait a couple of hours. We asked them to store our bags, and they did so by giving us the combination to the storage room. Four hours later a room was ready for us, but it definitely was not what we were promised. We finally were assigned a suite, and when we got there they were still cleaning the room!! There was a piece of garbage on the floor, and it was STILL there when we checked out (yes, it was in the middle of the floor in a very obvious place!). The water was NEVER cold (at best you could still make a cup of hot tea), which I think is a requirement in New Orleans in August. The concierge staff was very poorly informed, and I wondered if they had ever even left the hotel and explored the city. We asked for the nearest coffee shop one morning and were told that there was none? (Just as a point of reference, go out the door, make a left when you are standing at the corner look diagonal to you and there is a CiCi鈥檚. The best coffee you will find.) On the first night we ordered room service, we had 陆 of a sandwich left and fries. When we returned the following day the food was gone, but the plate/ tray/ dirty glasses were still there. For the rest of the trip we looked at that plate, in hopes that someone would realize that it should be sent somewhere. The furnishings in the rooms are the same as the ones from the Monaco, however they attempted (poorly) to make it look more plantation instead of fresh. All in all, I won鈥檛 be staying here again, nor will I recommend the Hilton Saint Charles to anyone. I hope that this is just a growing pain that they are experiencing, but I wont be back to see. 
