<Author>RoadWarriorOne
<Content>Not Recommended Although this hotel was recently renovated and looks like a four star hotel, the service and amenities are significantly inferior. Several times during our stay, we heard the excuse  We have only been open a month. This appeared to be the standard answer to all problems. If you feel compelled to stay at this hotel, I suggest visiting only after enough time has gone by (nine months to one year) and they can no longer use this as an excuse for poor service. The food on the Conceirge/Executive Level was horrible, stale and spoiled if they put any food out at all. They served prepackaged muffins that had expiration dates of May 1 , 2007 (I stayed at the hotel during 4th of July)...if staying on the Executive Level, you may have breakfast served or you may not - but don't rely on it. - not even coffee..the fitness center looks great, but only two of the cardio machines can actually be plugged in...then again, they've have only been open a month.In addition to the inferior service, the hotel charged me for my entire stay in advance, even though I was only informed that a deposit would be charged. My guess is that they have had guests check out early and this was their attempt to prevent that from occurring again. I certainly would have gladly repacked the next day and check-in o any of the other hotels close by if I had not already been charged in advance.I booked the room through the hotel reservation line for one rate and received a confirmation for my stay; however, when I arrived at the hotel, the room rate had increased by an additional $30! per night. Thankfully, I still have my email confirmation, so protesting the additional charges should not take much time...but I should not have to deal with this inconvenience.I travel often for work (usually 30 weeks per year) and would not stay at this hotel again. 
